## Limitations

The findings are based on available literature and may not encompass all possible perspectives or recent studies. The psychological impact of abortion is complex and can be influenced by numerous factors, including personal beliefs, societal norms, and support systems. Additionally, the safety and risks associated with abortion can vary significantly depending on the healthcare infrastructure and legal framework in different regions. Further research and longitudinal studies are needed to fully understand the long-term effects of abortion on women's health.

